![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/d8fdd173-f5a7-4ce6-971f-53a608793eb7/18338.jpg?format=original)

In a move that's sure to excite both wrestling and film fans, WWE superstar Drew McIntyre has officially joined the cast of the upcoming 'HIGHLANDER' reboot from Amazon MGM Studios’ United Artists. The Scottish Warrior will step into a significant role, starring opposite Henry Cavill as Angus MacLeod, brother to Cavill's character, Connor MacLeod.

This casting news adds another layer of anticipation to a project that has already garnered considerable attention. Henry Cavill's involvement as the lead was a major announcement, and now, with McIntyre joining the ranks, the film is building a formidable ensemble.

The original 'Highlander' film, released in 1986, became a cult classic, known for its iconic line "There can be only one," its unique premise of immortal warriors battling across centuries, and its memorable soundtrack by Queen. The story followed Connor MacLeod, a Scottish Highlander born in the 16th century, who discovers he is one of a select group of immortals who can only be killed by decapitation. These immortals are destined to fight each other until only one remains to claim "The Prize."

For Drew McIntyre, this role marks a significant foray into mainstream acting. While many WWE Superstars have transitioned to Hollywood, McIntyre's casting in a major franchise reboot alongside a star like Cavill speaks volumes about his growing presence and charisma beyond the wrestling ring. His powerful physique, commanding presence, and Scottish heritage make him a natural fit for the 'Highlander' universe, particularly as a MacLeod.

The addition of Angus MacLeod as Connor's brother promises to expand on the lore and familial dynamics that were hinted at in the original series. Fans will be eager to see how this sibling relationship plays out and what role Angus will have in Connor's journey through immortality. Given McIntyre's background, it's safe to assume that his character will be involved in some intense action sequences.

The 'HIGHLANDER' reboot is being directed by Chad Stahelski, known for his work on the 'John Wick' franchise, which bodes well for the film's action choreography and visual style. With a director adept at crafting intricate fight scenes and a cast featuring talent like Cavill and McIntyre, the new 'HIGHLANDER' is shaping up to be a visually stunning and action-packed revival of a beloved classic.

As production gears up, fans will undoubtedly be looking forward to more details, and perhaps even a glimpse of McIntyre in his full 'Highlander' regalia.